HEADWORD: Lath-shaped
<hw>Lath"-shaped`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a slender
elongated form, like a lath; -- said of the feldspar of certain igneous
rocks, as diabase, as seen in microscopic sections.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lathwork</ent>⟦br⟧
